commit.message:
Fix rate as dotted path to callable

The rate= keyword argument did not actually support the documented
behavior of allowing a dotted path to a callable. This implements that
behavior and aligns the implementation with the similar functionality
for callable keys.

Fixes #204

Update middleware examples to new-style

Updates the middleware example in the security chapter to new (>1.10)
style, and tweaks usage docs mentioning MIDDLEWARE_CLASSES setting.

[ci skip] docs-only

Throw if get_usage is called without enough info

get_usage (and thus is_ratelimited) either a group or an fn argument. If
neither is passed, throw ImproperlyConfigured, which is what we've used
for similar call site errors.

Fixes #53.
